evaluateAllConditionByType

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Object evaluateAllConditionByType(String ruleAssociationType,
                                                                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean returnMsgOn,
                                                                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer numberOfMsgs)
Evaluates rules of a certain type

Parameters:
ruleType - the rule type (e.g. "eligibility", "availability", "validation" or any custom types).
  • For validation rules, only "validation" is allowed.
  • For Boolean rules, ruleType can be a comma-delimited list (e.g. "eligibility,type1,type2")
    returnMessageOn - Boolean value to indicate when to return the message. By default it's false.
    numberOfMsgs - Number of messages returned. By default it's 1.
    Returns:
    Return value depends on the rule type
  • For validation rules, returns null if there are no validation errors, otherwise returns an ErrorList object
  • For eligibility, availability and other Boolean rules, returns true if all of the rules return true, false otherwise
    Examples in Javascript:
  • item.evaluateAllConditionByType("validation");
  • item.evaluateAllConditionByType("eligibility,customType"), where customType is a Boolean association type

    public CatalogItemItem findAssociation(String scode,
                                       com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean checkAvailability)
    Finds the item-item association object by association code. The resultset will be filtered based on the types or whether availability rules are checked

    Parameters:
    scode - The association code
    checkAvailability - If true, availability rule will be checked. If false, rule is not checked.
    Returns:
    The item-item association object, return null if not found.

    getAssociations

    public CatalogItemItem[] getAssociations(String[] types,
                                         com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean checkAvailability)
    Gets a list of item-item associations for this item. The resultset will be filtered based on the types or whether availability rules are checked. The invoking item will be assigned to theCatalogItem during execution of the API.

    Parameters:
    types - Array of item association types for filtering. If null, all item associations of this item will be returned
    checkAvailability - If true, availability rule will be checked. If false, rule is not checked. If input is null, availability rule will not be checked
    Returns:
    A list of item-item associations for this item

    public String[] getParentsByType(String associationTypeCode,
                                 Date reqTime)
    Gets item's parents for a given date. If an association type code is specified returns only the parents for the given association type code. Otherwise returns all parent codes.

    Parameters:
    associationTypeCode - The association type code. If null returns all parents

    Returns:
    Array of parent items codes or null

    price

    public ErrorList price(String[] currencies)
    Calculates the prices for this catalog item. To get list of calculated prices please use getCharges API.

    Parameters:
    String - [] represents the list of currencies code. For example, CAD. The list of currencies will be used to filter the charges that will be included in the pricing.
    Returns:
    null if the pricing operation is successful, or ErrorList object with the errors found during pricing.
    Throws:
    CwfException - code DE6242 will be throw if currency code enter is invalid
